    "body": "I agree. As far as I can tell, EIP 3074 would make this class of timelocks always bypassable.\r\n\r\nUPDATE: Actually; no it won‚Äôt. Bypass can still be prevented by requiring the receiver is an EOA, even after 3074. The key is that the bypass only works if the receiver address is an *immutable* contract. With 3074, an EOA can always unAUTH whatever they‚Äôve AUTHed, and so an EOA cannot be used to bypass a timelock even after 3074.",
